      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your frustration with wait times, but it's crucial to prioritize safety with warfarin. Even if your lifestyle and heart seem stable, your body's response to the medication can change, and unexpected complications can occur without regular monitoring. Lowering your dose without professional guidance increases the risk of adverse effects. It's best to continue with your current regimen and seek a timely consultation with your healthcare provider. Your health and safety are paramount. Keep focusing on your well-being!",
      "source": "target",
